 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bellia>Bellia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#333333>(1/23/03 11:38:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8552.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.belliapics.homestead.com/files/bellia.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet Discipline or Elemental Pact</span><hr size=1> Pet discipline enabled my little Trio group to hunt exp in PoV against enraging mobs at a rate of exp gain unable to obtain in any other zone or camp.  Better AA than my Dire Charm IMO. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Mistress Bellia Divinewind <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bcodeofsilence98698">&lt;Code of Silence&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Tinku's lvl 62 Phantasmist Pet<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=231078">I am ghetto</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhasinfirestorm@themagicianstower>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1252<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 3:15:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8552.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet Discipline or Elemental Pact</span><hr size=1> Pet Hold all the way. As stated, vs enraging mobs, it takes the cake. /pet hold, pet (even if it's tanking for a pet group) goes and sits in the corner, and waits while it gets stomped, instead of reamed inside and out by it's own hasted attack speed. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886&quot;"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ninjacorp.com/Rhasin_sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=itsastony>itsastony</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 250<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 3:49:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8552.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet Discipline or Elemental Pact</span><hr size=1> Hmmm, I would be very interested in knowing how /pet hold helps with the trials or enraging mobs. How do you use /pet hold in those situations and whats the benefit. I dont have /pet hold yet, but have 4 AAs in the mo and might decide to get it finally if the benefits would come clear to me ...<br>
<br>
Thx.<br>
<br>
Mel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kalahadbb>KalahadBB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 218<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 4:15:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8552.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet Discipline or Elemental Pact</span><hr size=1> When PoP came out I duod from 61-65 with a shaman in disease, then valor...Would have been *alot* harder without pet hold, as enrage would have torn the pets up alot more.  Elemental pact isn't that useful in my opinion, specualy since all the pets I use now dont take malachite anyways. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=526560" target="top"> Arch Convoker Kalahad Thundersoul</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ringofvalor.com">Ring of Valor</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=woonx>woonx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 308<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 4:18:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8552.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet Discipline or Elemental Pact</span><hr size=1> pet hold benefits<br>
<br>
1) No more &quot;no pets on this raid!&quot; from the guild leader. I'm mage officer in my guild and pretty much the authority on pets (I tell others when and how pets are allowed). Main exception with this are people with pet hold. If you have pet hold and can prove me you have at LEAST 2 neurones, I won't ever ask you to kill your pet unless you do something very very very stupid.<br>
<br>
2) Enrage. Let's say you are fighting a 600 hitting mob that enrage (pretty common if you raid) and it cast an aoe dot. So your pet is wackin on it with the rest of the raid and the mob reach 9% and enrage and start riposting all attack from the front, let's say also that your MT has trouble positioning the mob and your pet is hitting from the front. Well without pet hold, your pet will have great chances of dying, and you won't be able to do anything else than mash pet back off key because pet will keep wanting to go back on the mob because of the dot. Pet hold makes this very very simple.<br>
<br>
3) AoE mob pulls. Pet will sense AoEs through walls (flashback from ToV days) and pet disc will allow you to have pet up at all time without worrying about what's gonna be pulled next in places like ToV or VT.<br>
<br>
4) Pet tanking. with pet hold you can easily make your pet tank enraging mobs. Simply /pet guard here, /pet hold and let the mob enrage on your tanking pet without worry.<br>
<br>
